						<summary>

						<p>Pāṇḍya, Jaṭāvarman Sundarapāṇḍya I, Sunday, Hasta = A.D. 1251-70.</p>						

						<p>This much damaged record refers to the regnal years 11 to 13 of the Kāḍava chief Kōpperuñjiṅga. It seems that certain persons absconded without paying taxes <hi rend="italic">(kaḍamai)</hi> and those who stood surety <hi rend="italic">(puṇai)</hi> were held responsible for the taxes.</p>						

						</summary>
